            .</p>
               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="178506290077"></xptr>Prisoner. There is not the name of 
               <persName id="t17850629-62-person575">
                  Joseph
                   Smith
               <interp inst="t17850629-62-person575" type="surname" value="Smith"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17850629-62-person575" type="given" value="Joseph"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17850629-62-person575" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            ? - There are several more Smiths, numbers, but none of Richard.</p>
               <p>Jury. We wish to know whether this 
               <persName id="t17850629-62-person576">
                  Richard
                   Smith
               <interp inst="t17850629-62-person576" type="surname" value="Smith"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17850629-62-person576" type="given" value="Richard"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17850629-62-person576" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             is rated on the ship's books of the Prince George, as an able seaman? - No, he is not, he is not rated here, he is said to come from the Robust, he is a supernumerary man, he is a lent man to be returned again; entered as from the Robust.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17850629-62-person577">
                  THOMAS
                   FLETCHER
               <interp inst="t17850629-62-person577" type="surname" value="FLETCHER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17850629-62-person577" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
